ions can be answered by visiting the FAQ section in <br>the Legends website at:<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://legends.everquest.station.sony.com/showcase/home.jsp">legends.everquest.station...e/home.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br> <br>If you are a Legends subscriber and your questions is related to your <br>account or an in game issue please fill a webform request at the link <br>bellow and a Legends representative will assist you.  <br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.station.sony.com/services/everquest-contactgm.jhtml">www.station.sony.com/serv...ctgm.jhtml</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Additional Legends F.A.Q.:<br><br>Q: How much does the Legend's server cost to play monthly?<br>A: Legends costs $39.95 a month.<br><br>Q: Can I sign up for a longer period than one month?<br>A: Legends subscriptions will be on a recurring monthly basis. There are<br>no options for subscribing for other periods of time.<br><br>Q: If I register for the Legends server, when will my characters be <br>moved? <br>A: Once you have completed the registration process in the EverQuest <br>game client, we expect your character(s) to be transfered to the <br>EverQuest Legends service within a few hours by an automated script. You<br>should receive a confirmation e-mail once your character(s) have been <br>transferred. Each time you designate characters to be moved, you should <br>stay off of that account completely for a few hours so that the script <br>does not bypass your account (because the account is actively in the <br>game or in chat when the   script tries to modify it).<br>You should be aware that (i) some factors could interfere with <br>designated character moves   (for instance, our script is running while <br>your account is logged in the game or   in chat, which would interfere <br>with the move process), (ii) the level of   demand or other factors <br>might cause a delay in character moves, and (iii) this is a new service <br>and, accordingly, you should expect and anticipate glitches;   however, <br>we will work to get those glitches resolved on a reasonable basis.<br><br>Q: What if I cancel my Legends service, what happens to my characters?<br>A: We have posted a complete outline of the character move policies at <br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://legends.evequest.station.sony.com/showcase/movepolicy.jsp.">legends.evequest.station....olicy.jsp.</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Q: I already know that when I move a character to a Legends server I get<br>to keep all my stuff, titles, faction&amp; everything. But what if I cancel <br>and go back to my old server? Will the unique items that I've discovered<br>on the Legends server go with me?<br>A: Absolutely. Anything you earn on a Legends server you get to keep. We<br>also wanted to point out that all items that are unique to the Legends <br>server will be no-drop if moved to a non-Legends server on which such <br>items are still not available. If at some future date those items become<br>available on the servers, then any such items brought to the server <br>earlier may become dropable if the Live version of the item is also <br>dropable.<br><br><br>If this does not solve your issue, please email me back or contact our <br>phone support Mon.-Fri, 8:30 A.M.-5:30 P.M. PST, at (85<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> 537-0898.  <br>Please be sure to include your original message with all future <br>correspondence regarding this matter.<br><br>The Station Customer Service <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 388<br> <font col