tens of thousands of employees), if there was a customer service issue.. it didnt matter what department you were involved in or how high on the totem pole you sat.. everyone worked togethor to make things right. Oh and we didnt charge you more for that kind of service either. We did it because it was the right thing to do.<br><br>I feel bad for our GM on this server. It seems to me she tries really hard and does a great job all things considered. I wonder if she gets tired of having to tell folks, &quot;We are aware of this issue, please do a /bug report so they can have more testers look at it&quot;...these are the same testers that signed off the changes for regular servers I presume... I just wish they would have done those same tests for FV before they released the changes instead of after.<br><br><br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 3/25/02 3:05:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kloevis>Kloevis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/02 3:25:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How Verant cares about its customers</span><hr size=1> What really gets me going is how everytime there's a new patch, it winds up fucking up something else that didn't have problems before, EVERYTIME.<br>It's like they just don't even bother testing this shit out before they throw it at us, and now patches have gotten to the point of being a giant joke.<br><br>big patch=guarantee there will be &quot;emergency band-aid&quot; that'll send the servers down an additional day, but after people wind up with loss, etc.<br><br>I know EQ is only 10$ a month to play, but if I rent a video for 3$ and it's broken, I usually take it back, no problems.<br><br>I remember the whole Velius(sp?) and Luclin debacles.....wide awake fucking nightmares.<br>and worse still, you're directed to the &quot;tech board&quot;<br>and they don't tell you shit, except:<br>-blame your ISP.<br>-blame your rig.<br>-delete a post as SOON as someone makes a valid point/possible fix, then RE-post it like THEY were the ones who thought of it.<br>bullshit/beaurocracy at it's finest.<br>amazingly enough, Verant itself has a &quot;good&quot; rating on the BBB.<br>!!<br><br>Planes of Power is just going to be another months long nightmare before it works ok.<br><br>Guess that's all we can expect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukurley.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kurley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/02 3:54:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How Verant cares about its customers</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think people need to give Verant a bit of a break.  Like it or not, EQ is a business and it's run like one.  You can say VI doesn't care, they're pricks etc..etc..etc..however look at what they've given you:  THE best MMORPG on the market.  As Sony is now involved with the running of VI, it is run as a separate profit center, the operating results are reported to Sony.  To put things in perspective, VI = &lt; 3% of Sony's profitability, thus you better believe that EverQuest has to run tight numbers.<br><br>I find it funny that the same people who cry and whine about the bugs etc...are also the same people who you see posting stuff like &quot;I haven't been able to log on for 2 hours WTF?!?!?!&quot; or &quot;I can't stand not being able to log on!!!&quot;.  It's called biting the hand that feeds you.  If you honestly hate VI so much and hate the bugs in EQ, then just bloody quit the game. <br><br>&quot;What really gets me going is how everytime there's a new patch, it winds up fucking up something else that didn't have problems before, EVERYTIME.<br>It's like they just don't even bother testing this shit out before they throw it at us, and now patches have gotten to the point of being a giant joke.&quot;<br><br>Aye Kloevis, this stuff pisses me off too.  However I think people need to consider the following:  EQ is far more complex than people imagine.  Programming isn't a static, impervious structure.  When new variables and functions are entered into the system, they effect the variables and functions that existed before.  To presume that VI programmers could foresee every bug or problem that would arise from new code is like asking a set of parents to sit down and give a detailed account of the impact their unborn child will have on the world around it.<br><br>The other thing to consider is this:  the playtesters used for testing new expansions/patches are a relatively small group of players and they are not the best players using EQ - in essence they do not adequately &quot;stress test&quot; the system.<br><br>Look at automobiles - companies run them through rigorous testing and everything seems fine, however when they release them to the general population, the law of large numbers and the miriad stresses placed upon the vehicles when used in everyday applications reveals all kinds of shortcomings, defects and problems.  In this case, the automobiles are recalled etc...because they present a health risk.  In the case of Everquest, what the hell would people do if they shut down EQ for a couple of days?  They'd go berzerk.  <br><br>Think about this:  EQ has been running virtually everyday since release in 1999 and has been rigorously tested by the subscriber base since that time.  Any MMORPG that comes out will either a) have to pour over all the minute detailed bugs that plagued EQ, b) copy EQ's current playtested coding, c) be playtested for over a year to uncover any shortcommings, and/or d) be coded by God.  Translation, EQ and Sony's forthcoming MMORPG products have a head and shoulder's advantage over every other MMORPG that will come out - so you better get used to Sony's operating style or find something else to burn your life away.<br><br>EverQuest cost you 1.4 cents per hour to play.  I beg anyone to show me a comparable form of entertainment with the same intensity and longevity for that price, other than buying a porno movie in the discount bin that gets you off every time.<br><br>Noone forces anyone to play EQ.  It's a luxury.  If anyone thinks they are getting ripped off for $9.95 a MONTH...go to Starbucks and order a coffee and a danish - THAT is larceny.<br><br>Once you accept that you are addicted to EQ, everything becomes a tad more palatable.<br><br>Kurley Greenleaf<br>the Champion of Magic<br>CNN Correspondent <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kloevis>Kloevis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/02 4:05:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re