ested, and I mean tested for the different rulesets.. pvp, FV, etc. Once tested, THEN schedule the release and do the patch.<br><br>Your point about their testers not being the best EQ players is probably very true, but I honestly don't think you would have to be a good EQ player to realize TLC was f*cked up, or that the Alignments werent working properly on FV. You would probably just have to be as smart as a trained monkey. In fact it seems to me that Verant missing those two things just screams that they didnt bother to test any of that at all.<br><br>As far as profitability is concerned. I would argue that its cheaper to do things right the first time, then to have to bring in more people to do an emergency patch for a second straight nite in a row. How many patches in 2002 has there been now that have been immediately followed by an emergency patch the next day? How many folks does verant need to bring in (for a second straight night) to accomplish this? If this were my organization I certainly wouldnt tolerate this kind of sloppiness and lets not kid ourselves.. thats exactly what it is, sloppy.<br><br><br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 3/25/02 4:47:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/02 6:00:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How Verant cares about its customers</span><hr size=1> bah!<br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>